CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 4, 1953, pg. 2, reads: "Fetch Branding Irons - Branding Irons? Perhaps so. At least Dennis Walker of 2005 Webster Avenue is thinking about using them after his prize pinto, 'Champ,' was the victim of an East Liberty hoss thief last Saturday.  The desperado and the brown and white horse were corralled in 7300 block of Tioga Street Monday be East Liberty police. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Dennis Walker and his horse "Champ" standing beside wooden fence, Webster Avenue, Hill District
